{"parse":{"title":"International Association of Forensic Linguists","pageid":15198184,"revid":822551904,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>International Association of Forensic Linguists</b> (<b>IAFL</b>) is a professional organization consisting primarily of linguists working in fields related to the area of language and law, or <a href=\"/wiki/Forensic_linguistics\" title=\"Forensic linguistics\">forensic linguistics</a>. Areas of expertise include (but are not limited to) <a href=\"/wiki/Authorship_attribution\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Authorship attribution\">authorship attribution</a>, disputed confessions, trademark issues, legal language, etc. In addition to linguists, the association has members from other professions related to language and the law, particularly members of the legal profession. \nCurrently, the president of the IAFL is Janet Cotterill (<a href=\"/wiki/Cardiff_University\" title=\"Cardiff University\">Cardiff University</a>), and the vice-president is Ronald Butters (<a href=\"/wiki/Duke_University\" title=\"Duke University\">Duke University</a>).\n</p><p>The IAFL holds biennial international conferences and edits the <i>International Journal of Speech, Language and the Law</i> (formerly <i>Forensic Linguistics</i>), a peer-reviewed journal that publishes articles on any aspect of forensic language, speech and audio analysis. The board of editors includes language experts; Ronald Butters, Diana Eades, Paul Foulkes and Peter French.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Controversy\">Controversy</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Association_of_Forensic_Linguists&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Controversy\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 2008, lawyers hired by the one-man company <a href=\"/wiki/Nemesysco\" title=\"Nemesysco\">Nemesysco</a> threatened with legal actions unless the article \"Charlatanry in forensic speech science\",<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> published in <i>International Journal of Speech Language and the Law</i> in 2007, was withdrawn.<sup id=\"cite_ref-slashdot_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-slashdot-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The publisher Equinox decided to withdraw the article from the online version of the magazine, and offered the company to publish a letter in the journal, an offer they never took.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Publisher_note_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Publisher_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> In the article, a commercial product sold by the company was criticized as based on pseudo-science, and the company was not given the chance to comment before the article was published. The withdrawal resulted in criticism of the publisher for not understanding how to manage a scientific journal.<sup id=\"cite_ref-tysta_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-tysta-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_Swedish_Academy_of_Sciences\" title=\"Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences\">Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences</a> branded the company's behavior a \"serious assault on research freedom\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Citations\">Citations</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Association_of_Forensic_Linguists&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Citations\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Eriksson, Anders; Francisco Lacerda (2007). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.scribd.com/doc/9673590/Eriksson-Lacerda-2007\">\"Charlatanry in forensic speech science: A problem to be taken seriously\"</a>. <i>International Journal of Speech Language and the Law</i>. Equinox Publishing. <b>14</b> (2): 169\u2013193. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1558/ijsll.2007.14.2.169\">10.1558/ijsll.2007.14.2.169</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-02-02</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=International+Journal+of+Speech+Language+and+the+Law&amp;rft.atitle=Charlatanry+in+forensic+speech+science%3A+A+problem+to+be+taken+seriously&amp;rft.volume=14&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=169-193&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1558%2Fijsll.2007.14.2.169&amp;rft.aulast=Eriksson&amp;rft.aufirst=Anders&amp;rft.au=Francisco+Lacerda&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fdoc%2F9673590%2FEriksson-Lacerda-2007&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInternational+Association+of+Forensic+Linguists\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-slashdot-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-slashdot_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=09/01/29/2018254\">\"Lie Detector Company Threatens Critical Scientists With Suit\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Slashdot\" title=\"Slashdot\">Slashdot</a></i>. 2009-01-29<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-02-02</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Slashdot&amp;rft.atitle=Lie+Detector+Company+Threatens+Critical+Scientists+With+Suit&amp;rft.date=2009-01-29&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fyro.slashdot.org%2Farticle.pl%3Fsid%3D09%2F01%2F29%2F2018254&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInternational+Association+of+Forensic+Linguists\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Publisher_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Publisher_note_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Joyce, Janet (2008-12-04). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.equinoxjournals.com/ojs/index.php/IJSLL/article/view/3775\">\"Note from Publisher\"</a>. Equinox Publishing<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-02-02</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Note+from+Publisher&amp;rft.pub=Equinox+Publishing&amp;rft.date=2008-12-04&amp;rft.aulast=Joyce&amp;rft.aufirst=Janet&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.equinoxjournals.com%2Fojs%2Findex.php%2FIJSLL%2Farticle%2Fview%2F3775&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInternational+Association+of+Forensic+Linguists\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-tysta-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-tysta_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Bojs, Karin (2009-01-27). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20090203073347/http://www.dn.se/DNet/jsp/polopoly.jsp?d=1298&amp;a=877754\">\"They try to suppress research\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Dagens_Nyheter\" title=\"Dagens Nyheter\">Dagens Nyheter</a></i> (in Swedish). Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.dn.se/DNet/jsp/polopoly.jsp?d=1298&amp;